title: Persepolis
author: Marjane Satrapi
Subtitle: The Story of a Childhood and The Story of a Return

title: Oryx and Crake
author: Margaret Atwood
notes: Atwood's credentials as a writer of style and  substance show through. A recounting of an apocalyptic future as seen from an individual perspective. Not burdened down my lots of detail about the actual details of the event, instead choosing to create a mood and perspective that seems all too real.

title: Freakonomics

Subtitle: A Rogue Economist Explores the Hidden Side of Everything

title: Essential Classic X-Men, Vol. 3
author: Steve Englehart, Bob Brown, Marie Severin, Herb Trimpe, Sal Buscema, Jim Starlin, Gerry Conway, Gil Kane, Don Heck, Arnold Drake, Werner Roth, Tom Sutton, Roy Thomas, Neal Adams, Dennis O'Neil, Archie Goodwin, Linda Fite
Subtitle: (Marvel Essentials)

title: The Bedwetter
author: Sarah Silverman
Subtitle: Stories of Courage, Redemption, and Pee

title: The Elephant Vanishes
author: Haruki Murakami
Subtitle: (Panther S.)
notes: A very sparse and intriguing writing style had me curiously captivated. At the end of many of the stories I was by surprised by the brevity of the endings, yet not annoyed since the whole story had been strange and curious.

title: Stasiland
author: Anna Funder
Subtitle: Stories from Behind the Berlin Wall

title: Wide-Eyed and Legless
author: Jeff Connor
Subtitle: Inside the Tour de France
notes: Reasonably interesting coverage about the ill fated ANC-Halfords team, but not a huge amount of depth.
